<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sorsby</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-17"><hi rend="italic">April 17,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Claim all exemptions, privileges, and immunities accorded by Nicaragua by
                            treaty to consuls of any other most favored foreign nation. If none such
                            are accorded by treaty between Nicaragua and other foreign State, Clancy
                            may testify touching facts which came to his knowledge in his merely
                            personal and unofficial capacity, but not as to facts or communications
                            obtained in his capacity as consular agent. If he so testifies, report
                            to the Department copy of questions and answers.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>